===2010 census===
The [[2010 United States census]] counted 1,264 people, 529 households, and 354 families in the CDP. The [[population density]] was {{convert|442.0|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|people&nbsp;|people|}}. There were 573 housing units at an average density of {{convert|200.4|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}. The racial makeup was 71.76% (907) [[White (U.S. census)|White]], 12.82% (162) [[Black (U.S. census)|Black or African American]], 4.83% (61) [[Native American (U.S. census)|Native American]], 0.71% (9) [[Asian (U.S. census)|Asian]], 0.00% (0) [[Pacific Islander (U.S. census)|Pacific Islander]], 4.03% (51) from [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census|other races]], and 5.85% (74) from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. census)|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 8.07% (102) of the population.<ref name=Census2010>[http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3422530 DP-1 - Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics: 2010 Demographic Profile Data for Fairton CDP, New Jersey] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20200212143725/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/10_DP/DPDP1/1600000US3422530 |date=2020-02-12 }}, [[United States Census Bureau]]. Accessed November 2, 2012.</ref>

Of the 529 households, 23.4% had children under the age of 18; 45.4% were married couples living together; 16.3% had a female householder with no husband present and 33.1% were non-families. Of all households, 28.4% were made up of individuals and 12.7% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.39 and the average family size was 2.90.<ref name=Census2010/>

20.1% of the population were under the age of 18, 8.7% from 18 to 24, 23.3% from 25 to 44, 29.4% from 45 to 64, and 18.6% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 43.7 years. For every 100 females, the population had 92.7 males. For every 100 females ages 18 and older there were 89.1 males.<ref name=Census2010/>

===2000 census===
As of the [[2000 United States census]]<ref name="GR2" /> there were 2,253 people, 474 households, and 334 families residing in the CDP. The [[population density]] was {{convert|308.5|/km2|/mi2|disp=preunit|people|people|abbr=on}}. There were 511 housing units at an average density of {{convert|70.0|/km2|/mi2|disp=preunit|units|units|abbr=on}}. The racial makeup of the CDP was 61.43% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 33.38% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 2.35% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 1.20% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.18% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 1.46% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 11.54% of the population.<ref name=Census2000>[http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/00_SF1/DP1/1600000US3422530 DP-1 - Profile of General Demographic Characteristics: 2000 from the Census 2000 Summary File 1 (SF 1) 100-Percent Data for Fairton CDP, New Jersey] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.today/20200212095408/http://factfinder.census.gov/bkmk/table/1.0/en/DEC/00_SF1/DP1/1600000US3422530 |date=2020-02-12 }}, [[United States Census Bureau]]. Accessed November 2, 2012.</ref>

There were 474 households, out of which 26.8% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 53.0% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 11.8% had a female householder with no husband present, and 29.5% were non-families. 24.9% of all households were made up of individuals, and 11.4% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.46 and the average family size was 2.92.<ref name=Census2000/>

In the CDP the population was spread out, with 11.5% under the age of 18, 9.0% from 18 to 24, 48.0% from 25 to 44, 23.3% from 45 to 64, and 8.3% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 36 years. For every 100 females, there were 265.7 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 313.9 males.<ref name=Census2000/>

The median income for a household in the CDP was $37,962, and the median income for a family was $41,000. Males had a median income of $30,750 versus $25,326 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $20,005. About 3.1% of families and 5.9% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 4.6% of those under age 18 and none of those age 65 or over.<ref name=Census2000/>

